    "Only a single iteration per question was performed, and the results were accepted as final.",
    "Future studies could use a temperature setting of 1.0 and multiple iterations to better evaluate consistency and provide a more robust statistical analysis of GPT-4's accuracy in summative assessments.",
    "An important consideration in the use of LLMs such as GPT-4 in medical and educational settings is the \"black box\" problem.",
    "This issue refers to the opacity in how these models make decisions or generate responses, thus making it difficult to understand the underlying reasoning processes.",
    "This lack of transparency can be problematic, particularly in high-stakes environments-such as education and health care-where reliability and accountability are paramount."
